26#include <sys/cdefs.h>
27__KERNEL_RCSID(0, "$NetBSD: nouveau_nvkm_subdev_i2c_pad.c,v 1.3 2018/08/27 07:38:42 riastradh Exp $");
28
29#include "pad.h"
30
31static void
32nvkm_i2c_pad_mode_locked(struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad, enum nvkm_i2c_pad_mode mode)
33{
34 PAD_TRACE(pad, "-> %s", (mode == NVKM_I2C_PAD_AUX) ? "aux" :
35 (mode == NVKM_I2C_PAD_I2C) ? "i2c" : "off");
36 if (pad->func->mode)
37 pad->func->mode(pad, mode);
38}
39
40void
41nvkm_i2c_pad_mode(struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad, enum nvkm_i2c_pad_mode mode)
42{
43 PAD_TRACE(pad, "mode %d", mode);
44 mutex_lock(&pad->mutex);
45 nvkm_i2c_pad_mode_locked(pad, mode);
46 pad->mode = mode;
47 mutex_unlock(&pad->mutex);
48}
49
50void
51nvkm_i2c_pad_release(struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad)
52{
53 PAD_TRACE(pad, "release");
54 if (pad->mode == NVKM_I2C_PAD_OFF)
55 nvkm_i2c_pad_mode_locked(pad, pad->mode);
56 mutex_unlock(&pad->mutex);
57}
58
59int
60nvkm_i2c_pad_acquire(struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad, enum nvkm_i2c_pad_mode mode)
61{
62 PAD_TRACE(pad, "acquire");
63 mutex_lock(&pad->mutex);
64 if (pad->mode != mode) {
65 if (pad->mode != NVKM_I2C_PAD_OFF) {
66 mutex_unlock(&pad->mutex);
67 return -EBUSY;
68 }
69 nvkm_i2c_pad_mode_locked(pad, mode);
70 }
71 return 0;
72}
73
74void
75nvkm_i2c_pad_fini(struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad)
76{
77 PAD_TRACE(pad, "fini");
78 nvkm_i2c_pad_mode_locked(pad, NVKM_I2C_PAD_OFF);
79}
80
81void
82nvkm_i2c_pad_init(struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad)
83{
84 PAD_TRACE(pad, "init");
85 nvkm_i2c_pad_mode_locked(pad, pad->mode);
86}
87
88void
89nvkm_i2c_pad_del(struct nvkm_i2c_pad **ppad)
90{
91 struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad = *ppad;
92 if (pad) {
93 PAD_TRACE(pad, "dtor");
94 list_del(&pad->head);
95#ifdef __NetBSD__
96 linux_mutex_destroy(&pad->mutex);
97#else
98 mutex_destroy(&pad->mutex);
99#endif
100 kfree(pad);
101 pad = NULL;
102 }
103}
104
105void
106nvkm_i2c_pad_ctor(const struct nvkm_i2c_pad_func *func, struct nvkm_i2c *i2c,
107 int id, struct nvkm_i2c_pad *pad)
108{
109 pad->func = func;
110 pad->i2c = i2c;
111 pad->id = id;
112 pad->mode = NVKM_I2C_PAD_OFF;
113#ifdef __NetBSD__
114 linux_mutex_init(&pad->mutex);
115#else
116 mutex_init(&pad->mutex);
117#endif
118 list_add_tail(&pad->head, &i2c->pad);
119 PAD_TRACE(pad, "ctor");
120}
121
122int
123nvkm_i2c_pad_new_(const struct nvkm_i2c_pad_func *func, struct nvkm_i2c *i2c,
124 int id, struct nvkm_i2c_pad **ppad)
125{
126 if (!(*ppad = kzalloc(sizeof(**ppad), GFP_KERNEL)))
127 return -ENOMEM;
128 nvkm_i2c_pad_ctor(func, i2c, id, *ppad);
129 return 0;
130}
